<paragraph pageNumber="102">
This is an uncommon Central European species which has occurred in North Germany and Poland and also Belgium and the Netherlands. The worker is like that of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:29673" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" genus.bestMatchDistance="760" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Lasius bicornis (Förster)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">L. bicornis</taxonomicName>
, but has the dorsum of the gaster as well as alitrunk crowded with long hairs and the scale with a more angular emargination. Queens and males have similar differences and are much larger than 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:29673" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" genus.bestMatchDistance="721" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Lasius bicornis (Förster)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">L. bicornis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
